01:16:01.090 --> 01:16:06.150
Graduate English address,
A Kind of Destiny.

01:16:06.150 --> 01:16:08.980
Candidate for the
degree of Master

01:16:08.980 --> 01:16:12.040
in Public Policy,
Philip A Harding.

01:16:29.790 --> 01:16:32.410
Over two centuries
ago, a man came

01:16:32.410 --> 01:16:38.590
to Harvard uncertain of
his future and his fate.

01:16:38.590 --> 01:16:41.900
He had received an offer
he could not refuse,

01:16:41.900 --> 01:16:46.940
and though he felt unworthy,
he wrote to his family

01:16:46.940 --> 01:16:50.580
that he believed
a kind of destiny

01:16:50.580 --> 01:16:53.820
was driving him to Cambridge.

01:16:53.820 --> 01:16:58.680
He spent his first night right
here sleeping in Harvard Yard,

01:16:58.680 --> 01:17:05.240
and awoke the next
morning-- July 3, 1775--

01:17:05.240 --> 01:17:09.640
to take command of the troops
of the United Provinces of North

01:17:09.640 --> 01:17:16.040
America, the fledgling
Continental Army.

01:17:16.040 --> 01:17:20.380
George Washington had a unique
Harvard application process.

01:17:23.410 --> 01:17:28.520
His admissions committee was
the Second Continental Congress.

01:17:28.520 --> 01:17:31.000
And his experience
here at Harvard

01:17:31.000 --> 01:17:36.000
would not only define the
final 24 years of his life,

01:17:36.000 --> 01:17:43.370
but the startup he
launched here would go on

01:17:43.370 --> 01:17:47.780
to change the course
of human history.

01:17:47.780 --> 01:17:52.490
Just across the street, under a
tree, is a group of monuments,

01:17:52.490 --> 01:17:56.230
one displaying rows of
strapping uniformed soldiers

01:17:56.230 --> 01:17:58.640
welcoming Washington
to Cambridge.

01:17:58.640 --> 01:18:01.010
And another says,
under this tree,

01:18:01.010 --> 01:18:03.910
Washington first took command
of the American army--

01:18:03.910 --> 01:18:07.730
July 3, 1775.

01:18:07.730 --> 01:18:09.635
And I've always
felt a sense of awe

01:18:09.635 --> 01:18:13.010
for this world changing spot.

01:18:13.010 --> 01:18:15.910
But then I did some
research, and I

01:18:15.910 --> 01:18:18.033
found something less romantic.

01:18:20.660 --> 01:18:25.940
Washington's Harvard welcome
weekend was less than grand,

01:18:25.940 --> 01:18:29.750
and his first year Harvard
was downright awful.

01:18:29.750 --> 01:18:33.650
On Sunday, July 2, he
rode in to a deserted

01:18:33.650 --> 01:18:39.910
looking town soaking
wet and half sick.

01:18:39.910 --> 01:18:43.420
In fact, the welcome reception
was canceled due to rain.

01:18:43.420 --> 01:18:45.620
And several soldiers
wrote in their journals

01:18:45.620 --> 01:18:53.010
that nothing new or remarkable
happened on July 3rd.

01:18:53.010 --> 01:18:56.390
Imagine if we could go back in
time to this very spot that day

01:18:56.390 --> 01:18:58.780
in 1775.

01:18:58.780 --> 01:19:01.740
We would be sitting in
a very different Harvard

01:19:01.740 --> 01:19:08.420
Yard, a field full of makeshift
tents, un-uniformed soldiers,

01:19:08.420 --> 01:19:13.610
and a rough defense position
in place of Lamont Library.

01:19:13.610 --> 01:19:15.540
One historian
described this scene

01:19:15.540 --> 01:19:20.260
like Woodstock, New York 1969.

01:19:20.260 --> 01:19:23.930
A volunteer undisciplined,
under-equipped militia

01:19:23.930 --> 01:19:26.880
of farmers and merchants.

01:19:26.880 --> 01:19:30.290
This was the group,
about half the size

01:19:30.290 --> 01:19:32.900
of the crowd we've
assembled this morning,

01:19:32.900 --> 01:19:34.730
this was the group
that Washington

01:19:34.730 --> 01:19:39.480
came to lead against the
most powerful military force

01:19:39.480 --> 01:19:42.570
on Earth.

01:19:42.570 --> 01:19:45.990
But Washington took what was
offered to him here at Harvard

01:19:45.990 --> 01:19:48.244
and he made the most of it.

01:19:48.244 --> 01:19:49.910
And I'm not just
talking about the brass

01:19:49.910 --> 01:19:52.430
doorknobs, or the metal roof
he took off Harvard hall

01:19:52.430 --> 01:19:57.250
to melt into musket balls--
which they did take.

01:19:57.250 --> 01:20:04.680
But he took ideas that existed
only as words and writings

01:20:04.680 --> 01:20:11.190
and he turned them into reality
for millions and generations

01:20:11.190 --> 01:20:11.690
to come.

01:20:15.630 --> 01:20:18.690
And less than a year later,
after pushing the British out

01:20:18.690 --> 01:20:22.700
of Boston, Washington
received an honorary degree

01:20:22.700 --> 01:20:29.580
from this fine institution,
his first academic degree.

01:20:29.580 --> 01:20:32.380
And like many
Harvard graduates, he

01:20:32.380 --> 01:20:36.010
went on to take a prominent
position in New York City.

01:20:43.250 --> 01:20:46.920
And it almost killed him.

01:20:46.920 --> 01:20:48.800
Well, the British
nearly killed him.

01:20:48.800 --> 01:20:52.450
And we almost lost
the entire war.

01:20:52.450 --> 01:20:56.180
In fact, the next seven
years of the war effort

01:20:56.180 --> 01:20:59.612
would become the most
challenging years of his life.

01:21:02.340 --> 01:21:08.420
Today, you will receive a
piece of paper representing

01:21:08.420 --> 01:21:11.890
your short time here at Harvard.

01:21:11.890 --> 01:21:16.860
Your successes, your failures,
your all night study sessions,

01:21:16.860 --> 01:21:21.135
your lessons, your
first A minus.

01:21:27.480 --> 01:21:33.000
And the friendships that
will last a lifetime.

01:21:33.000 --> 01:21:34.760
Through these
experiences, you've

01:21:34.760 --> 01:21:39.240
developed, practiced, and
honed the skills you need.

01:21:39.240 --> 01:21:45.030
But sitting here today, facing
an uncertain future-- let alone

01:21:45.030 --> 01:21:48.040
the examples of mayors and
entrepreneurs, Nobel Prize

01:21:48.040 --> 01:21:51.430
winners, presidents,
and a queen,

01:21:51.430 --> 01:22:00.320
the queen of soul--
sitting here today

01:22:00.320 --> 01:22:03.380
facing a lot of uncertainty
and a lot of high bars,

01:22:03.380 --> 01:22:05.610
it might seem
difficult to connect

01:22:05.610 --> 01:22:09.340
the dots to your destiny.

01:22:09.340 --> 01:22:11.070
But have faith.

01:22:11.070 --> 01:22:15.290
Because there is a kind of
destiny waiting to be fulfilled

01:22:15.290 --> 01:22:19.079
that is uniquely yours.

01:22:19.079 --> 01:22:21.120
You see, Washington had
to go through a difficult

01:22:21.120 --> 01:22:24.670
transformation process, even
after receiving his Harvard

01:22:24.670 --> 01:22:28.330
degree, to turn
his kind of destiny

01:22:28.330 --> 01:22:33.540
into a real force that
could change history.

01:22:33.540 --> 01:22:38.480
And he came to discover
he could not do it alone.

01:22:38.480 --> 01:22:40.710
The individuals
and incidents that

01:22:40.710 --> 01:22:43.330
faced him over the
next seven years

01:22:43.330 --> 01:22:46.380
whittled, carved,
and sculpted him

01:22:46.380 --> 01:22:51.460
into the monumental
man we remember today.

01:22:51.460 --> 01:22:53.660
And in the end,
the army he thought

01:22:53.660 --> 01:22:57.550
he was coming to
transform ended up

01:22:57.550 --> 01:23:00.620
being the force that
transformed him.

01:23:03.210 --> 01:23:05.684
And while you may
not realize it yet,

01:23:05.684 --> 01:23:07.100
some of the biggest
lessons you'll

01:23:07.100 --> 01:23:09.570
take with you from
this experience

01:23:09.570 --> 01:23:15.610
have come from the people who've
been learning right beside you.

01:23:15.610 --> 01:23:16.800
They've challenged you.

01:23:16.800 --> 01:23:17.820
They've pushed you.

01:23:17.820 --> 01:23:19.600
They've inspired you.

01:23:19.600 --> 01:23:22.880
They've supported
you, and ultimately

01:23:22.880 --> 01:23:27.045
helped reveal a better
version of yourself.

01:23:30.060 --> 01:23:32.320
You see, the
question is not only

01:23:32.320 --> 01:23:36.784
what you will take with you,
but who you will take with you.

01:23:39.450 --> 01:23:45.600
On July 4, 1775, still a full
year before the Declaration

01:23:45.600 --> 01:23:49.570
of Independence, Washington
issued his first general orders

01:23:49.570 --> 01:23:52.120
to the troops from right
here in Harvard Yard,

01:23:52.120 --> 01:23:55.260
declaring that all
distinctions of colonies

01:23:55.260 --> 01:24:01.470
should be laid aside so that one
spirit may animate the whole,

01:24:01.470 --> 01:24:06.100
and the only contest
be who shall render,

01:24:06.100 --> 01:24:09.850
on this great and trying
occasion, the most

01:24:09.850 --> 01:24:13.990
essential service to this
great and common cause

01:24:13.990 --> 01:24:18.030
in which we are all engaged.

01:24:18.030 --> 01:24:20.430
And just as Washington
came here to Harvard

01:24:20.430 --> 01:24:24.760
to unite the 13 colonies, we've
come together this morning

01:24:24.760 --> 01:24:30.700
to celebrate the unity and
diversity of our 13 schools.

01:24:30.700 --> 01:24:33.310
Whether you are driven to
solve the world's largest

01:24:33.310 --> 01:24:39.140
public or private problems,
cure that dreaded disease,

01:24:39.140 --> 01:24:44.120
alleviate human suffering, work
across religious and cultural

01:24:44.120 --> 01:24:50.305
divides, generate knowledge
and push education forward.

01:24:50.305 --> 01:24:55.540
[CHEERING]

01:24:55.540 --> 01:24:58.708
Create effective
legal frameworks.

01:24:58.708 --> 01:25:01.690
[CHEERING]

01:25:01.690 --> 01:25:05.050
Design and construct the
future world we live in.

01:25:05.050 --> 01:25:08.340
[CHEERING]

01:25:08.340 --> 01:25:11.940
Or use technology to enable new
discoveries and innovations.

01:25:11.940 --> 01:25:14.766
[CHEERING]

01:25:19.010 --> 01:25:24.760
Whatever kind of destiny
is compelling you today,

01:25:24.760 --> 01:25:29.835
imagine the countless lives that
are waiting for you to step up.

01:25:32.950 --> 01:25:37.440
In two centuries, who might be
talking about the grand mission

01:25:37.440 --> 01:25:41.370
you begin today in this yard?

01:25:41.370 --> 01:25:45.490
Who will be saying
they sat right there

01:25:45.490 --> 01:25:48.090
under that tree in that spot?

01:25:50.850 --> 01:25:54.740
Let today be your moment to
accept the challenge that

01:25:54.740 --> 01:25:56.850
has been offered to you.

01:25:56.850 --> 01:26:00.250
Bring that most
essential service only

01:26:00.250 --> 01:26:05.360
you can provide to this
great and common cause.

01:26:05.360 --> 01:26:10.245
And together, let us not
just go change the world,

01:26:10.245 --> 01:26:15.688
but let us go serve
the world with passion.

