exemplar of academic values

02:07:16.400 --> 02:07:21.870
and common sense in the
governance of the university.

02:07:21.870 --> 02:07:24.780
After a childhood in
the segregated south,

02:07:24.780 --> 02:07:29.600
she came to Massachusetts
to attend Wheaton College.

02:07:29.600 --> 02:07:33.590
She went on to Harvard
Law School in an era

02:07:33.590 --> 02:07:37.270
when the doors of legal
education and practice

02:07:37.270 --> 02:07:41.970
had barely begun to open
for African American women.

02:07:41.970 --> 02:07:44.780
She pursued her
devotion to civil rights

02:07:44.780 --> 02:07:48.800
in positions at the Equal
Employment Opportunity

02:07:48.800 --> 02:07:52.060
Commission and the
Department of Justice

02:07:52.060 --> 02:07:56.330
before launching a four decade
career at the Georgetown

02:07:56.330 --> 02:07:59.440
University Law Center.

02:07:59.440 --> 02:08:03.370
