University in St. Louis.

02:14:16.230 --> 02:14:22.230
A prolific researcher, he
helped introduce co-evolution,

02:14:22.230 --> 02:14:26.130
a seminal concept in
evolutionary biology.

02:14:26.130 --> 02:14:29.230
He has also made
fundamental contributions

02:14:29.230 --> 02:14:33.690
in biogeography, folk taxonomy,
and pollution studies.

02:14:36.280 --> 02:14:40.100
A distinguished teacher, he
has written leading textbooks

02:14:40.100 --> 02:14:43.370
on both botany and
the environment

02:14:43.370 --> 02:14:47.520
and mentored scores
of grateful students.

02:14:47.520 --> 02:14:50.170
An energetic citizen
of science, he

02:14:50.170 --> 02:14:53.400
has been a central figure in
the work of both the National

02:14:53.400 --> 02:15:00.290
Academy of Sciences and the
National Geographic Society.

02:15:00.290 --> 02:15:04.630
Recognized worldwide for his
leadership in conservation

02:15:04.630 --> 02:15:10.580
and sustainability, he has been
elected to scientific academies

02:15:10.580 --> 02:15:15.710
in nearly 20 nations, from
Denmark to New Zealand,

02:15:15.710 --> 02:15:19.280
from Brazil to India.

02:15:19.280 --> 02:15:24.750
He helped lead a massive
project to classify the 31,500

02:15:24.750 --> 02:15:28.060
species of plants
in China and has

02:15:28.060 --> 02:15:31.450
been a catalyst for
international scientific

02:15:31.450 --> 02:15:34.360
collaboration.

02:15:34.360 --> 02:15:38.750
We salute a man who in
the words of one admirer

02:15:38.750 --> 02:15:42.960
has touched the whole world
with the power of science

02:15:42.960 --> 02:15:49.001
and the moral imperative of the
conservation of life-- Peter

02:15:49.001 --> 02:15:49.995
Raven.

02:15:49.995 --> 02:15:53.474
[APPLAUSE]

02:16:04.920 --> 02:16:09.280
A grand sycamore in
the garden of science,

02:16:09.280 --> 02:16:14.510
he has nourished our knowledge
of the phyla of flora

02:16:14.510 --> 02:16:19.240
and cultivated care for the
precious diversity of life--

02:16:19.240 --> 02:16:23.320
Peter Hamilton Raven,
Doctor of Science.

02:16:23.320 --> 02:16:26.792
[APPLAUSE]

02:16:37.240 --> 02:16:41.400
Maybe the most important
reason for writing

02:16:41.400 --> 02:16:44.059
is to prevent the
erosion of time

02:16:44.059 --> 02:16:48.129
so that memories will not
be blown away by the wind,

02:16:48.129 --> 02:16:50.510
our next guest has said.

02:16:50.510 --> 02:16:55.490
We should write what
should not be forgotten.

02:16:55.490 --> 02:16:59.480
Her own vivid works of
imagination and remembrance

02:16:59.480 --> 02:17:02.540
will not be forgotten
by countless readers

02:17:02.540 --> 02:17:04.809
around the world.

02:17:04.809 --> 02:17:08.809
Born in Peru, raised
largely in Chile,

02:17:08.809 --> 02:17:11.870
she had a turbulent childhood.

02:17:11.870 --> 02:17:16.346
In time, she made her way as a
journalist and talk show host

02:17:16.346 --> 02:17:16.846
in Santiago.

02:17:19.959 --> 02:17:24.780
On September 11,
1973, a violent coup

02:17:24.780 --> 02:17:29.620
felled President Salvador
Allende, her cousin.

02:17:29.620 --> 02:17:32.430
Suddenly everything changed.

02:17:32.430 --> 02:17:41.490
By 1975, she was in exile in
Venezuela building a new life.

02:17:41.490 --> 02:17:46.590
In 1981, she learned that
her beloved grandfather,

02:17:46.590 --> 02:17:51.480
still living in
Chile, was dying.

02:17:51.480 --> 02:17:54.260
The letter she set
out to write him

02:17:54.260 --> 02:17:58.430
grew into her first novel,
The House of the Spirits,

02:17:58.430 --> 02:18:03.049
a landmark in Latin American
fiction and a testament

02:18:03.049 --> 02:18:07.120
to Chile's tumultuous times.

02:18:07.120 --> 02:18:11.440
She has gone on to
write 20 books in all,

02:18:11.440 --> 02:18:15.660
emerging as one of the Western
hemisphere's most illustrious

02:18:15.660 --> 02:18:18.379
authors.

02:18:18.379 --> 02:18:22.940
Her stories mix
history with fantasy,

02:18:22.940 --> 02:18:28.139
the intensely political
with the fiercely personal,

02:18:28.139 --> 02:18:33.530
the strikingly real with
the hauntingly surreal.

02:18:33.530 --> 02:18:37.330
Her several memoirs reflect
with candor and wonder

02:18:37.330 --> 02:18:42.610
on her own life experience,
including the devastating death

02:18:42.610 --> 02:18:45.230
of her daughter
Paula, in whose memory

02:18:45.230 --> 02:18:48.350
she maintains a
charitable foundation

02:18:48.350 --> 02:18:51.760
to promote the welfare of
women and children worldwide.

02:18:54.950 --> 02:18:58.629
Her lyrical style has
been described as packed

02:18:58.629 --> 02:19:02.070
with action, prodigal
in invention,

02:19:02.070 --> 02:19:05.370
vivid in description
and metaphor.

02:19:05.370 --> 02:19:08.389
Her stories, as
one critic writes,

02:19:08.389 --> 02:19:11.820
have moved the readers of
Latin American literature

02:19:11.820 --> 02:19:16.280
in ways that few authors have.

02:19:16.280 --> 02:19:19.190
We honor Isabel Allende.

02:19:19.190 --> 02:19:22.130
[APPLAUSE]

02:19:41.280 --> 02:19:45.740
Conjuring memories
blown by winds of exile,

02:19:45.740 --> 02:19:49.630
leavening realism
with dashes of magic,

02:19:49.630 --> 02:19:53.500
she fills her splendorous
house of stories

02:19:53.500 --> 02:19:58.040
with spirits and shadows,
anguish and love.

02:19:58.040 --> 02:20:01.390
Isabel Allende,
Doctor of Letters.

02:20:01.390 --> 02:20:04.330
[APPLAUSE]

02:20:16.600 --> 02:20:22.260
This stage has been graced by
presidents and prime ministers,

02:20:22.260 --> 02:20:27.410
laureates and literary lights,
even the occasional prince

02:20:27.410 --> 02:20:30.060
or king.

02:20:30.060 --> 02:20:34.700
In fact, with us here today, we
have a president, a laureate,

02:20:34.700 --> 02:20:39.600
a literary luminary,
and even a King.

02:20:39.600 --> 02:20:42.230
We now proudly welcome
to this esteemed company

02:20:42.230 --> 02:20:45.130
her regal highness,
the queen of soul.

02:20:45.130 --> 02:20:48.567
[APPLAUSE]

02:21:01.824 --> 02:21:05.670
Born in Memphis,
raised in Detroit,

02:21:05.670 --> 02:21:09.050
she was a child prodigy
with a voice that

02:21:09.050 --> 02:21:13.120
shook the rafters of her church.

02:21:13.120 --> 02:21:18.970
As a teenager, she set out
on gospel caravan tours

02:21:18.970 --> 02:21:20.950
with her father.

02:21:20.950 --> 02:21:23.990
She soon had a
recording contract.

02:21:23.990 --> 02:21:28.380
And within a few years, she was
not just climbing the charts,

02:21:28.380 --> 02:21:32.640
but topping them with
five straight singles that

02:21:32.640 --> 02:21:36.740
sold more than a
million copies each.

02:21:36.740 --> 02:21:40.710
Over the years, her records
helped compose the soundtrack

02:21:40.710 --> 02:21:47.930
of a generation--
"Respect," "Chain of Fools,"

02:21:47.930 --> 02:21:56.570
"I Never Loved a Man," "Baby,
I Love You," "Think Until you

02:21:56.570 --> 02:22:03.380
Come Back to Me," "Spanish
Harlem," and on and on.

02:22:03.380 --> 02:22:08.300
She has won an eye
popping 18 Grammy awards.

02:22:08.300 --> 02:22:11.102
[APPLAUSE]

02:22:13.910 --> 02:22:16.940
Including the award
for best female

02:22:16.940 --> 02:22:24.060
R&amp;B vocal performance for an
amazing eight straight years.

02:22:24.060 --> 02:22:28.900
Her voice has galvanized three
presidential inaugurations,

02:22:28.900 --> 02:22:33.660
and it graced the funeral of
Doctor Martin Luther King.

02:22:33.660 --> 02:22:38.320
The first woman inducted into
the Rock and Roll Hall of Fame,

02:22:38.320 --> 02:22:43.940
and a recipient of the
National Medal of Arts,

02:22:43.940 --> 02:22:48.070
she was presented in 2005
with the nation's highest

02:22:48.070 --> 02:22:52.490
civilian honor-- the
Presidential Medal of Freedom.

02:22:52.490 --> 02:22:55.920
[APPLAUSE]

02:22:59.360 --> 02:23:04.150
Her vocal virtuosity
is so admired

02:23:04.150 --> 02:23:07.610
that her home state of
Michigan declared her voice

02:23:07.610 --> 02:23:10.130
one of the state's
natural resources.

02:23:10.130 --> 02:23:13.870
[LAUGHTER]

02:23:13.870 --> 02:23:16.760
There are singers,
Ray Charles once said,

02:23:16.760 --> 02:23:20.550
and then there is Aretha.

02:23:20.550 --> 02:23:25.710
With the utmost respect--
I won't spell it out--

02:23:25.710 --> 02:23:28.330
we honor Aretha Franklin.

02:23:28.330 --> 02:23:31.318
[APPLAUSE]

02:23:59.720 --> 02:24:01.340
Hey band, do that again.

02:24:01.340 --> 02:24:03.380
We couldn't hear you
with the cheering.

02:24:03.380 --> 02:24:09.356
[LAUGHTER]

02:24:09.356 --> 02:24:12.344
[BAND PLAYING - ARETHA FRANKLIN,
 "RESPECT"]

02:24:31.766 --> 02:24:35.252
[CHEERING]

02:24:39.240 --> 02:24:44.790
Almighty fire and amazing
grace, she reigned sublime

02:24:44.790 --> 02:24:48.890
as the electrifying
empress of soul.

02:24:48.890 --> 02:24:53.510
For this, our highest honor,
she is a natural woman.

02:24:53.510 --> 02:24:56.328
Aretha Franklin, Doctor of Arts.

02:24:56.328 --> 02:24:59.262
[APPLAUSE]

02:25:15.410 --> 02:25:18.970
Our next guest's
singular career has

02:25:18.970 --> 02:25:22.850
combined extraordinary
entrepreneurial success,

02:25:22.850 --> 02:25:27.250
distinguished public service,
and visionary philanthropy

02:25:27.250 --> 02:25:29.840
for the common good.

02:25:29.840 --> 02:25:33.720
Born across the river at
Saint Elizabeth's Hospital

02:25:33.720 --> 02:25:38.500
in Allston/Brighton,
raised in nearby Medford,

02:25:38.500 --> 02:25:42.820
he worked his way through
college at Johns Hopkins

02:25:42.820 --> 02:25:46.170
before earning his MBA at
Harvard Business School.

02:25:46.170 --> 02:25:51.420
[CHEERING]

02:25:51.420 --> 02:25:53.900
Wall Street beckoned.

02:25:53.900 --> 02:25:58.550
He soon became a rising star in
equity trading and information

02:25:58.550 --> 02:26:04.050
systems, and then launched
the firm that bears his name.

02:26:04.050 --> 02:26:09.080
The rise of Bloomberg
LP, transformed the world

02:26:09.080 --> 02:26:11.740
of financial information.

02:26:11.740 --> 02:26:14.910
And it established
its founder as one

02:26:14.910 --> 02:26:17.860
of the nation's most
savvy executives

02:26:17.860 --> 02:26:21.460
and imaginative entrepreneurs.

02:26:21.460 --> 02:26:24.240
Having built his company
into a global force,

02:26:24.240 --> 02:26:29.210
he set his sights on a
new leadership challenge.

02:26:29.210 --> 02:26:35.560
Three times, he won election as
mayor of the City of New York,

02:26:35.560 --> 02:26:44.020
serving from 2002 until December
of 2013 Over that 12 year

02:26:44.020 --> 02:26:49.660
tenure, he dedicated himself to
enhancing the city's schools,

02:26:49.660 --> 02:26:57.940
spurring the creation of new
jobs, improving public health,

02:26:57.940 --> 02:27:03.150
nourishing the arts and culture,
and confronting the challenge

02:27:03.150 --> 02:27:07.560
of climate change, all while
helping the city navigate

02:27:07.560 --> 02:27:12.180
the wrenching aftermath of 9/11.

02:27:12.180 --> 02:27:17.120
As a philanthropist, he has
devoted more than 3.3 billion

02:27:17.120 --> 02:27:20.010
and counting of
his own resources

02:27:20.010 --> 02:27:25.780
to an array of worthy causes,
education foremost among them.

02:27:25.780 --> 02:27:29.510
[APPLAUSE]

02:27:29.510 --> 02:27:33.770
Few figures in our time
have made so strong a mark

02:27:33.770 --> 02:27:37.780
on both business and government.

02:27:37.780 --> 02:27:41.120
On both the vitality
of private enterprise

02:27:41.120 --> 02:27:45.900
and the creative pursuit
of the public good,

02:27:45.900 --> 02:27:50.160
let us honor his honor
Michael Bloomberg.

02:27:50.160 --> 02:27:53.590
[APPLAUSE]

02:27:53.590 --> 02:27:56.530
[BAND PLAYING]

02:28:14.210 --> 02:28:17.700
From Hopkins to
Harvard, Wall Street

02:28:17.700 --> 02:28:23.780
to City Hall, a resolute leader
and fervent philanthropist,

02:28:23.780 --> 02:28:29.220
whose entrepreneurial spirit
and zeal for innovation

02:28:29.220 --> 02:28:34.339
have helped our
nation's burg to bloom,

02:28:34.339 --> 02:28:38.251
Michael Bloomberg,
Doctor of Laws.

02:28:38.251 --> 02:28:41.674
[APPLAUSE]

02:28:55.855 --> 02:28:59.900
It is seldom on
this stage that we

02:28:59.900 --> 02:29:02.290
take the occasion to
honor a former member

02:29:02.290 --> 02:29:05.125
of the cheerleading
squad at Yale.

02:29:05.125 --> 02:29:09.860
[LAUGHTER]

02:29:09.860 --> 02:29:12.970
But there is more to this story.

02:29:12.970 --> 02:29:21.440
Born in Milton, Massachusetts
90 years ago next month,

02:29:21.440 --> 02:29:23.890
he served with valor
and distinction

02:29:23.890 --> 02:29:28.729
as a Navy pilot in the
Pacific during World War II.

02:29:28.729 --> 02:29:31.687
[CHEERING]

02:29:39.090 --> 02:29:44.110
In 1945, he married his
sweetheart, Barbara Pierce.

02:29:44.110 --> 02:29:46.768
[APPLAUSE]

02:29:55.460 --> 02:29:59.100
Soon after, he enrolled
in a quaint college

02:29:59.100 --> 02:30:03.350
in the hinterlands of
South Central Connecticut

02:30:03.350 --> 02:30:07.290
in a city that stakes
its claim to fame

02:30:07.290 --> 02:30:09.613
on being the birthplace
of the lollipop.

02:30:16.600 --> 02:30:21.080
He kept in Yale's baseball team
as a left handed first baseman,

02:30:21.080 --> 02:30:24.520
and he led them to the finals
of the College World Series

02:30:24.520 --> 02:30:25.900
two years in a row.

02:30:32.240 --> 02:30:35.240
When Babe Ruth presented
an original manuscript

02:30:35.240 --> 02:30:38.280
of his autobiography
to the Yale archives,

02:30:38.280 --> 02:30:41.940
our guest was chosen
to receive it.

02:30:41.940 --> 02:30:47.090
By the 1960s, in Texas, he
launched his remarkable career

02:30:47.090 --> 02:30:49.914
in public service.

02:30:49.914 --> 02:30:56.120
[APPLAUSE]

02:30:56.120 --> 02:30:58.650
Across the decades,
it would take him

02:30:58.650 --> 02:31:01.110
from the House of
Representatives

02:31:01.110 --> 02:31:05.720
to service as US Ambassador
to the United Nations,

02:31:05.720 --> 02:31:09.350
from chairing the Republican
National Committee to directing

02:31:09.350 --> 02:31:15.110
Central Intelligence, from
eight years as vice president

02:31:15.110 --> 02:31:21.340
to his election in 1988 as the
41st president of the United

02:31:21.340 --> 02:31:22.149
States.

02:31:22.149 --> 02:31:25.143
[APPLAUSE]

02:31:33.640 --> 02:31:37.170
With a clear eye
and a steady hand,

02:31:37.170 --> 02:31:40.660
he led the United States
through a transformative time

02:31:40.660 --> 02:31:42.810
in world affairs.

02:31:42.810 --> 02:31:46.720
His presidency saw the
liberation of Kuwait,

02:31:46.720 --> 02:31:55.290
the fall of the Berlin Wall, the
crumbling of the Soviet Union,

02:31:55.290 --> 02:31:58.810
the signing of the first
two Strategic Arms Reduction

02:31:58.810 --> 02:32:02.523
treaties, and the
end of the Cold War.

02:32:02.523 --> 02:32:05.421
[APPLAUSE]

02:32:11.220 --> 02:32:15.010
He was a force behind the
historic North American Free

02:32:15.010 --> 02:32:16.880
Trade Agreement.

02:32:16.880 --> 02:32:20.400
Working with Congress, he
championed the Americans

02:32:20.400 --> 02:32:24.870
with Disabilities Act, the
Clean Air Act amendments,

02:32:24.870 --> 02:32:27.490
the Community and
National Service Act,

02:32:27.490 --> 02:32:30.150
and the Immigration Act of 1990.

02:32:30.150 --> 02:32:33.030
[APPLAUSE]

02:32:36.390 --> 02:32:40.100
And throughout his long
career in public service,

02:32:40.100 --> 02:32:42.860
extending well beyond
his presidency,

02:32:42.860 --> 02:32:47.160
he has been a champion of
volunteer service for the well

02:32:47.160 --> 02:32:48.820
being of others.

02:32:48.820 --> 02:32:52.530
What he has famously
called Points of Light--

02:32:52.530 --> 02:32:55.385
or as they like to say in
New Haven, Points of Looks.

02:32:58.390 --> 02:33:01.310
With a burst of Eli
cheer, we proudly

02:33:01.310 --> 02:33:06.138
honor the honorable George
Herbert Walker Bush.

02:33:06.138 --> 02:33:09.132
[APPLAUSE]

02:33:09.132 --> 02:33:12.625
[BAND PLAYING]

02:33:44.570 --> 02:33:51.620
With faith, courage, and service
true, his eyes ever fixed

02:33:51.620 --> 02:33:55.800
on points of light,
he piloted our nation

02:33:55.800 --> 02:33:58.270
through changeful skies.

02:33:58.270 --> 02:34:01.940
His cap was blue,
his house was white,

02:34:01.940 --> 02:34:05.128
and now his robe is crimson.

02:34:05.128 --> 02:34:09.610
George H W Bush, Doctor of Laws.

02:34:09.610 --> 02:34:12.598
[APPLAUSE]

02:34:28.560 --> 02:34:32.160
In the name of this
society of scholars,

02:34:32.160 --> 02:34:36.600
I declare that these persons
are entitled to the rights

02:34:36.600 --> 02:34:41.100
and privileges pertaining
to their several degrees,

02:34:41.100 --> 02:34:44.450
and that their names
are to be forever borne

02:34:44.450 --> 02:34:47.440
on its role of honorary members.

02:34:51.320 --> 02:34:54.715
[APPLAUSE]

02:35:01.040 --> 02:35:05.420
Degree candidates and
their guests and all alumni

02:35:05.420 --> 02:35:08.160
are warmly invited to
attend the afternoon

02:35:08.160 --> 02:35:11.630
session of commencement
day exercises

02:35:11.630 --> 02:35:16.590
under the direction of the
Harvard Alumni Association.

02:35:16.590 --> 02:35:21.240
The alumni parade
will begin at 1:45 PM,

02:35:21.240 --> 02:35:25.280
and the exercises
will begin at 2:30 PM.

02:35:25.280 --> 02:35:29.840
The commencement speakers
will be Michael R Bloomberg

02:35:29.840 --> 02:35:33.230
and the president of
Harvard University.

02:35:33.230 --> 02:35:35.760
Now, the commencement
choir director

02:35:35.760 --> 02:35:39.350
will lead us in the singing
of the commencement hymn.

02:35:39.350 --> 02:35:42.150
Following the hymn,
the Pusey Minister

02:35:42.150 --> 02:35:44.770
will pronounce the benediction.

02:35:44.770 --> 02:35:48.750
The commencement exercises
then being ended,

02:35:48.750 --> 02:35:51.760
the Sheriff of
Middlesex County will

02:35:51.760 --> 02:35:54.600
declare the meeting adjourned.

02:35:54.600 --> 02:35:57.610
The audience is requested
to remain seated

02:35:57.610 --> 02:36:01.160
until the president and
fellows and their guests

02:36:01.160 --> 02:36:02.810
have withdrawn
from the platform.

02:36:06.802 --> 02:36:10.295
[BAND PLAYING]

02:36:20.275 --> 02:36:23.768
[MUSIC - SAMUEL GILMAN, "FAIR
 HARVARD"]

02:38:10.554 --> 02:38:15.560
[CHEERING]

02:38:15.560 --> 02:38:20.220
As we close this
morning's ceremony,

02:38:20.220 --> 02:38:23.690
I would like to offer
a benediction inspired

02:38:23.690 --> 02:38:27.310
by one of the greatest
intellectuals, poets,

02:38:27.310 --> 02:38:32.350
and preachers of the 20th
century, the Reverend Clarence

02:38:32.350 --> 02:38:36.530
Lavaughn Franklin, whose
daughter we honored here today.

02:38:39.440 --> 02:38:45.160
As an eagle stirreth
her nest, Oh God,

02:38:45.160 --> 02:38:51.230
we ask that you would stir
us to be kind and give thanks

02:38:51.230 --> 02:38:53.850
every day.

02:38:53.850 --> 02:39:00.910
Stir us, oh God, to
treat our bodies well.

02:39:00.910 --> 02:39:04.470
For we are made in the
imago dei, the image of God.

02:39:07.410 --> 02:39:11.570
Be kind, be of service.

02:39:11.570 --> 02:39:18.800
Stir us, oh God, to treat
our neighbors right.

02:39:18.800 --> 02:39:21.650
Stir us.

02:39:21.650 --> 02:39:23.970
Stir us so that we
might discipline

02:39:23.970 --> 02:39:28.710
ourselves to know
ourselves better.

02:39:28.710 --> 02:39:30.910
And in knowing
ourselves better, we

02:39:30.910 --> 02:39:36.470
begin to love
ourselves as we are.

02:39:36.470 --> 02:39:41.320
And when we break through the
cloud of insecurity that often

02:39:41.320 --> 02:39:45.050
confines our
bodies, then we will

02:39:45.050 --> 02:39:51.270
be able to love our
neighbors as ourselves.

02:39:51.270 --> 02:39:53.860
Stir us.

02:39:53.860 --> 02:40:02.550
Stir us, so that we
might, in humble ways,

02:40:02.550 --> 02:40:09.090
bring your kingdom here on
Earth as it is in heaven.

02:40:09.090 --> 02:40:11.456
May we all say together, amen.

02:40:26.396 --> 02:40:29.882
[CHEERING]

02:40:41.834 --> 02:40:50.642
As the high sheriff
of Middlesex County,

02:40:50.642 --> 02:40:57.474
I declare that the
meeting will be adjourned.

02:40:57.474 --> 02:41:02.354
[APPLAUSE]

02:41:02.354 --> 02:41:06.290
[BELL RINGS]

02:41:06.290 --> 02:41:08.910
Now the bell in the
church begins to ring.

02:41:08.910 --> 02:41:17.100
And there is a tintinnabulation
of bells all over Cambridge,

02:41:17.100 --> 02:41:19.550
including the great Lowell
House bells from Russia.

02:41:19.550 --> 02:41:22.269
And there's the Sheriff of
Middlesex County and Drew

02:41:22.269 --> 02:41:25.990
Faust, president of Harvard
leading the procession.

02:41:25.990 --> 02:41:26.990
Procession of overseers.

02:41:26.990 --> 02:41:30.094
This is a grand
board of overseers,

02:41:30.094 --> 02:41:31.940
and Alan Garber, the provost.

02:41:31.940 --> 02:41:34.180
Everybody's heading
off the stage.

02:41:34.180 --> 02:41:36.600
And there will be a
president's spread.

02:41:36.600 --> 02:41:38.950
All of these luncheons
are called spreads.

02:41:38.950 --> 02:41:41.700
And they take place everywhere.

02:41:41.700 --> 02:41:47.540
The president's over near
Lowell House on Quincy Street.

02:41:47.540 --> 02:41:50.450
This has been an amazing
day in Harvard Yard,

02:41:50.450 --> 02:41:56.760
beginning with the influx of
so many students, and faculty,

02:41:56.760 --> 02:41:58.562
and parents, and families.

02:41:58.562 --> 02:41:59.520
And just extraordinary.

02:41:59.520 --> 02:42:01.520
If you just look at
all the happy faces,

02:42:01.520 --> 02:42:04.260
all the amazing achievement
of all of our students,

02:42:04.260 --> 02:42:07.606
and the celebration
of their current

02:42:07.606 --> 02:42:09.518
and also future accomplishments.

02:42:09.518 --> 02:42:11.407
It's just such an exciting time.

02:42:11.407 --> 02:42:11.990
And thank you.

02:42:11.990 --> 02:42:15.385
Here we see Aretha Franklin
being congratulated.

02:42:15.385 --> 02:42:16.660
And the Harvard Band.

02:42:16.660 --> 02:42:20.184
Actually, I think we should
note that the Latin orator is

02:42:20.184 --> 02:42:25.496
a member of the Harvard Band
when he put on that Roman hat

02:42:25.496 --> 02:42:28.484
for his oration.

02:42:28.484 --> 02:42:31.120
The faculty are filing
up to congratulate

02:42:31.120 --> 02:42:33.670
the honorary degree recipients.

02:42:33.670 --> 02:42:36.367
This afternoon,
this will fill again

02:42:36.367 --> 02:42:39.890
with the Harvard Alumnae
Association Annual

02:42:39.890 --> 02:42:42.610
Meeting, which will
be called to order.

02:42:42.610 --> 02:42:44.830
The new Alumnae
Association president

02:42:44.830 --> 02:42:49.500
is Cynthia Torres, who was
elected rather recently.

02:42:49.500 --> 02:42:59.320
And 1980 graduate of the college
who welcomed the newest class

02:42:59.320 --> 02:43:00.430
yesterday afternoon.

02:43:00.430 --> 02:43:03.322
So Diana, it's been a really
wonderful commencement,

02:43:03.322 --> 02:43:06.600
and I'm glad I got to
spend it with you here.

02:43:06.600 --> 02:43:08.770
We're just the talking
heads here of course.

02:43:08.770 --> 02:43:11.058
There's an entire crew of
people-- Kathy O'Connell

02:43:11.058 --> 02:43:13.540
and lots of other
people who are helping

02:43:13.540 --> 02:43:17.240
make this commencement happen
and make this broadcast happen.

02:43:17.240 --> 02:43:19.342
It's always a
pleasure to witness

02:43:19.342 --> 02:43:21.030
this spectacle with you.

02:43:21.030 --> 02:43:23.836
And it's such a great
pleasure to see the joy

02:43:23.836 --> 02:43:27.263
on the faces of the
graduates, and at the delight

02:43:27.263 --> 02:43:29.570
of the faculty of
being here as well

02:43:29.570 --> 02:43:34.180
to be reminded by our
student speakers of both

02:43:34.180 --> 02:43:38.980
the historic presence of
George Washington in this yard,

02:43:38.980 --> 02:43:44.670
and the inspiration that
the call to a global world

02:43:44.670 --> 02:43:46.600
really has for our students.

02:43:46.600 --> 02:43:49.204
We heard that again
and again this year.

02:43:49.204 --> 02:43:52.750
And I suspect it's
really part of why

02:43:52.750 --> 02:43:54.110
we're all here at Harvard.

02:43:54.110 --> 02:43:55.370
And the call to service.

02:43:55.370 --> 02:43:56.450
So thank you everyone.

02:43:56.450 --> 02:43:59.990
And we look forward to
seeing you again next year.

02:43:59.990 --> 02:44:02.730
Happy day of commencement.

